Access Systems wrote:
(Re my tightening lugnut sequence)  This is done in 2 stages,
> > one just to get the nut seated in its recess, and finally to really sock it tight....
> 
> I actually do it in three stages, one to snug up the nut, one to get it
> tight then I lower the wheel onto the ground some and really get it socked
> down tight.

OK, I forgot to mention I lower the car and then do the "sock it
tight"....wound never do that on the jack....But the sequence does
insure the rim centers into the tapered nuts, and I often go back to #1
to check it's drawn up. 
